Entry.JapaneseText: ねえねえ、<Tytree>が言ってた <Cyan>三つ星<White>って、どういう意味？
Entry.EnglishText: Hey hey, what did you mean by <Cyan>three stars<White>?

Entry.JapaneseText: まあまあ、って事かな？ 最高の場合は<Cyan>五つ星<White>だ。
Entry.EnglishText: Kinda average, I guess? The highest ranking is <Cyan>five stars<White>.

Entry.JapaneseText: じゃあ、最低だと<Cyan>ひとつ星<White>ってコト？
Entry.EnglishText: So, does that mean that if something's the worst, it gets <Cyan>one star<White>?

Entry.JapaneseText: ノンノンノンノン……最低なヤツには、 星は一個たりともやれないな。
Entry.EnglishText: Nononono... The worst things don't even get a single star.

Entry.JapaneseText: 使いたかったら、 <Mao>も使っていいぜ！
Entry.EnglishText: If you want to use it, then go right ahead!
